  <section class='fd-faq' id='f4'>
    <p class='fd-faqheader'>Where is (CBD) produced in the hemp plant?</p>
    <div class='fd-answer'>
      <ul>
        <li>Its primarily produced in trichomes (sac like structures that are part of the flower)</li>
        <li>Like all the cannabinoids, its produced as an acid.  In the case of CBD, as CBDA (cannabidiolic acid)</li>
        <li>CBDA is converted to CBD with light exposure, heat, and aging</li>
        <li>CBD is the most studied form, but there is emerging evidence that CBDA is a much more potent anti-inflammatory, and possibly anti-cancer molecule.</li>
      </ul>
