  <section class='fd-faq' id='f6'>
    <p class='fd-faqheader'>What is the difference between pure CBD; CBD included in a Full Spectrum Extract; and the entourage effect?</p>
    <div class='fd-answer'>
      <ul>
        <li>Pure CBD has a narrow, bell shaped therapeutic index, requiring high doses to get an effect, with the effect peaking and tapering off quickly with higher doses. <strong>Typical doses are in the 5-20 mg/kg/day for approved indications (up to 50 mg/kg have been used for seizure control).</strong></li>
        <li>Full spectrum extract containing CBD and the full range of biologically active compounds found in the trichomes requires a much lower dose <strong>(typically in the range of 0.5 to 1 mg/kg/day)</strong> for the same effect, with a much wider therapeutic window.
          <ul>
            <li>This is referred to as the entourage effect.</li>
            <li>There is a growing body of evidence that this is clinically relevant</li>
            <li>The evolving field of synergistic network pharmacology, moving past the single molecule, single target model of drug discovery, is ideally suited to further explore this effect</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
