    <p class='fd-faqheader'>Has the FDA approved pure CBD for use in any medicines?</p>
    <div class='fd-answer'>
      <ul>
        <li>Yes. It has approved Epidiolex (Cannabidiol), manufactured by GW Pharmaceuticals, for certain seizure disorders in children: Lennox-Gastaut syndrome; Dravet syndrome; Tuberous Sclerosis Complex.  The mechanism of action is uncertain, but felt to be related to:
          <ul>
            <li>Inhibition of Adenosine uptake</li>
            <li>Antagonism of GPR55</li>
            <li>Activation of TRPV1</li>
            <li>Inhibitory effects on Na+ and low voltage Ca++ channels</li>
