  <section class='fd-faq' id='f10'>
    <p class='fd-faqheader'>Can CBD be applied on the skin?</p>
    <div class='fd-answer'>
      <ul>
        <li>Yes, but CBD is not water soluble and cannot penetrate into the dermis and subcutaneous tissues.</li>
        <li>If the intended effect is related to deeper tissues, an absorption enhancer such as Argan Oil, needs to be added to topical formulation.
          <ul>
            <li>Argan Oil contains 40-50% Oleic Acid, and 30-40% Linoleic Acid, both of which disrupt the skin barrier and allow deeper penetration</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
