  <section class='fd-faq' id='f12'>
    <p class='fd-faqheader'>Does CBD interact with other medications?</p>
    <div class='fd-answer'>
      <ul>
        <li>There are potential interactions between prescription doses of CBD (pure CBD taken in much higher doses than contained in products made from Full Spectrum Extract) and drugs that are metabolized by CYP1A2; CYP2B6; CYP2C9; CYP2C19; and CYP3A4.</li>
        <li>There have been few reports of significant interactions between prescription drugs and sublingual or topical doses of CBD contained in products made from Full Spectrum Extract.</li>
        <li>The main interactions to watch for would be CBD with drugs with a narrow therapeutic index (NTI) metabolized by the same enzymes.  Penn State pharmacy recently published a list of 57 medications to monitor.  Commonly prescribed drugs on the list include:
          <ul>
            <li>Warfarin</li>
            <li>Levothroxin</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li class='fd-callout-text'>See the reference below for the full Penn State list of NTI medications to monitor.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class='fd-references'>
        <p class='print-hidden'><strong>External References</strong></p>
