  <section class='fd-faq' id='f13'>
    <p class='fd-faqheader'>What Precautions are there?</p>
    <div class='fd-answer'>
      <ul>
        <li>The following is based on <a href='#f9'>experience with Sativex</a> in Canada and Europe.  <strong>See the reference below for full information.</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Use in patients with moderate to severe hepatic impairment is not advised.  If used in patients with mild hepatic impairment, LFTs should be monitored to confirm no adverse effect on the liver.  CBD related effects are reversible when CBD use is discontinued.</li>
            <li>Use in patients with severe cardiovascular disease is not advised</li>
            <li>Patients with impaired renal function should be monitored for side effects</li>
            <li>Do not use in women who are pregnant or breast feeding</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Many of the precautions, like those related to a personal, or family history of psychiatric illness, are related to the THC contained in Sativex.  There is emerging evidence that CBD has a positive or neutral effect on these conditions.</li>
        <li>Products made from Full Spectrum Extract can contain small amounts of THC which can be detected in high sensitivity drug screening.  If patients are subject to drug testing, they should be made aware of this prior to taking these products</li>
      </ul>
      <div class='fd-references print-hidden'>
