  <section class='fd-faq' id='f15'>
    <p class='fd-faqheader'>What evidence is there that CBD is effective in treating defined medical conditions?</p>
    <div class='fd-answer'>
      <ul>
        <li>Researchers have identified a large number of receptors, enzymes, and membrane transporters that CBD interacts with, and the effects of those interactions, in human and animal models.  This is an essential first step, but not sufficient to demonstrate clinical efficacy.</li>
        <li>With the potential mechanisms of action identified, clinical uses of CBD is a hot research topic currently, with some well designed clinical trials currently being conducted in the US and other countries, focused on its use in a wide range of conditions.</li>
        <li>Most clinical trials reported to date have small numbers of participants, and with few exceptions are not randomized, controlled, blinded trials, which is the standard for proving efficacy.</li>
        <li>Evidence to date is that CBD is safe in doses used in the reported trials.</li>
      </ul>
